\cos{(a + b)} = \cos{a} \cos{b} - \sin{a} \sin{b}
\cos{(a - b)} = \cos{a} \cos{b} + \sin{a} \sin{b}
\implies \cos{(a + b)} + \cos{(a - b)} = 2 \cos{a} \cos{b}
\int_0^1 dx \, \cos{(4 \pi x)} \cos{(n \pi x)} = \frac12 \int_0^1 dx \, \cos{\left (n+4 \right )\pi x} +\frac12  \int_0^1 dx \, \cos{\left (n-4 \right )\pi x} 
n \ge 1
